text: Imperial County is a county in the state of California. It is in the United States. At the 2020 census, 179,702 people lived there. The county seat is El Centro. Imperial County is in the southeast corner of California. It is next to Mexico and Arizona. Of all the people in Imperial County, 73.7% speak Spanish at home. The economy of Imperial County depends on farming (agriculture). ==References== Category:1907 establishments in California
